H0.text: Plasma makes up most of the universe.

H1.text: Carbon is the type of matter that makes up most of the universe.

H2.text: Liquid is the type of matter that makes up most of the universe.

H3.text: Gas is the type of matter that makes up most of the universe.

A4.text: The great majority of ordinary matter in the universe is unseen, since visible stars and gas inside galaxies and clusters account for less than 10 percent of the ordinary matter contribution to the mass–energy density of the universe.

A5.text: The universe is composed almost completely of dark energy, dark matter, and ordinary matter, with ordinary matter contributing only 4.9% to the total mass–energy density of the universe.
